Anonymous Fri 21 Feb 2020 03:43:19 No.28502065 Report

>>28501642
First I use Relationship Dialogue Overhaul RDO, which adds follower dialogue for a lot of character types, but most importantly; follower/marriage dialogue for female khajiits and follower dialogue for female argonians
https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/74568/?

Then i have the console commands from 'Make Nearly anyone your follower-marriagable' manually installed
https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36520/?
This helps to cut down on having to remember the whole change faction nonsense and just simplifies it to selecting her or nearly any npc and typing "bat setfriend" (for follower) and/or "bat setmarry" (for marriage candidate)

And I personally use Extensible Follower Framework for my follower overhaul
https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/12933/?

This is the easiest way I've found from testing (2 mods which are great on their own and simplified console commands), but I wouldn't be surprised if there were other simplified methods. Just have to be prepared for possible bugginess (both from the mod and from quest/general skyrim buginess)

I'm not sure of the status of these mods in Special Edition since I still play Legendary, so might be something worth checking (doubtful EFF is working right now due to Special edition's SKSE constantly getting fucked when creation club stuff rolls in)
